==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nonviolent
<hw>nonviolent</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>peacefully
resistant in response to injustice; not using violence; -- used of
protests and demonstrations; <as>as, <ex>nonviolent</ex>
resistance</as>. Opposite of <ant>violent</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> passive, peaceful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>achieved without bloodshed. Contrasted with
<ant>bloody</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unbloody, bloodless.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nonviscid</ent>⟦br⟧
